TITLE: Simple Option Unpacking with ? Operator in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates basic usage of the ? operator to handle an Option<u8> and return an Option<String>. The function adds 1 to the age if present, or returns None if the input is None.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-by-example.git/blob/master/src/error/option_unwrap/question_mark.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
fn next_birthday(current_age: Option<u8>) -> Option<String> {
    // If `current_age` is `None`, this returns `None`.
    // If `current_age` is `Some`, the inner `u8` value + 1
    // gets assigned to `next_age`
    let next_age: u8 = current_age? + 1;
    Some(format!("Next year I will be {}", next_age))
}
```

