TITLE: Demonstrating Variable Capture Methods in Rust Closures
DESCRIPTION: Shows different ways closures can capture variables including immutable references, mutable references, and value ownership. Demonstrates borrowing rules and mutation restrictions with practical examples using String, counter, and Box types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-by-example.git/blob/master/src/fn/closures/capture.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
fn main() {
    use std::mem;

    let color = String::from("green");

    let print = || println!("`color`: {}", color);

    print();

    let _reborrow = &color;
    print();

    let _color_moved = color;


    let mut count = 0;
    let mut inc = || {
        count += 1;
        println!("`count`: {}", count);
    };

    inc();

    inc();

    let _count_reborrowed = &mut count; 


    let movable = Box::new(3);

    let consume = || {
        println!("`movable`: {:?}", movable);
        mem::drop(movable);
    };

    consume();
}
```

