TITLE: Implementing Shared Ownership Between Threads Using Arc in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use Arc to share a string value across multiple threads. It creates an Arc-wrapped string, spawns 10 threads that each clone the Arc reference, and prints the shared value from each thread. The program uses thread::sleep to ensure all spawned threads complete before the main thread exits.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-by-example.git/blob/master/src/std/arc.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
