TITLE: Implementing Lifetime Bounds with Debug Trait in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of lifetime bounds in Rust through a generic struct Ref and two printing functions. Shows how to specify lifetime constraints on generic types and references, while also implementing the Debug trait. The example includes both direct and reference-based generic function implementations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-by-example.git/blob/master/src/scope/lifetime/lifetime_bounds.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

