TITLE: Demonstrating Variable Scope in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how variable bindings have different scopes in Rust. It illustrates a long-lived binding in the main function and a short-lived binding within a nested block. The code also demonstrates that variables are not accessible outside their scope.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-by-example.git/blob/master/src/variable_bindings/scope.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
fn main() {
    // This binding lives in the main function
    let long_lived_binding = 1;

    // This is a block, and has a smaller scope than the main function
    {
